# Git Push Strategy

## Branch Layout

- `rh-develop`: working branch, contains internal deploy files (`rh_config.json`, `sync.sh`)
- `main`: release branch, must NOT contain these files

## Push to main

NEVER push `rh-develop:main` directly. Always use this workflow:

```bash
# 1. Create/update local main from rh-develop
git checkout -B main rh-develop

# 2. Remove internal files from main
git rm --cached rh_config.json sync.sh
git commit -m "chore: exclude internal deploy files from main"

# 3. Push main to both remotes
git push origin main
powershell.exe -NoProfile -Command "git push github main"

# 4. Switch back to working branch
git checkout -f rh-develop
```

## Push to rh-develop (Gitea only)

```bash
git push origin rh-develop
```

## Remotes

| Remote | Push branches |
|--------|---------------|
| `origin` (Gitea) | `rh-develop` + `main` |
| `github` (GitHub) | `main` only, via `powershell.exe` |
